World oil prices dropped despite Hurricane Rita approaching the Gulf of Mexico.
OPEC promised increased crude supply if needed.
New York's main contract for October delivery fell to $66.30 per barrel.
Rita upgraded to a category two hurricane, threatening the US Southeast.
Airlines suspended flights, and evacuations were underway in Florida, Louisiana, and Texas.
Rita's potential impact on Texas and Louisiana raised concerns.
The Florida Keys faced evacuation orders.
Rita's path towards the Gulf of Mexico could lead to further strengthening.
Emergency preparations were in place, with fears of a Category 4 hurricane hitting Texas.
